'''Loading Screens''' are a series of intermittent scenes that are shown when loading into the client or [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds|worlds]]. It displays helpful tips about VRChat, as well as display a download progress bar.

== Client ==
The background of the loading screen is determined by Cosmetics. A graphic containing various prompts is displayed in the center of the screen. Below it, the world download progress percentage is shown.

The background of the loading screen is determined by Cosmetics. A graphic containing various prompts is displayed in the center of the screen. Below it, the world download progress percentage is shown.

The button area at the bottom may display the following buttons: Return to Home/Go to default Home and GO!. Return to Home/Go to default Home and GO! may appear together.<gallery perrow="5">
File:None.png|1. Entering VRChat Home with “Show Go Button On Load” disabled. No buttons displayed.
File:GO!.png|2. Entering any world with “Show Go Button On Load” enabled. “GO!” 
File:Return to Home.png|3. Entering a non-VRChat Home that is not a custom Home. “Return to Home”
File:Go to default Home.png|4. Entering a non-VRChat Home that is a custom Home. “Go to default Home”
</gallery>After downloading, the loading screen will display the thumbnail of the world with a load indicator below it. The load indicator states progress in this order: 

* "'''Initializing World...'''", "'''Connecting...'''", "'''Joining...'''", and "'''Almost Done!'''"<small>{verify}</small> if the loading takes too long.

While in VR, you are able to see a mirrored version of the loading screen by looking behind.

