== Settings for the loading screen ==

==== "Go!" button ====
Within the [[Main Menu]] [[Settings]] menu, under the '''User Interface''' tab, there is an option to toggle a "Go!" button on load. Having this setting enabled requires the user to click the Go button before loading into the world. Disabling the setting will remove the Go button, causing you to automatically join when the download is completed.

==== Preloading worlds ====
When browsing a world's page from within the VRChat client, an Action that can be clicked is '''Preload World'''. By preloading a world before joining, most of the loading screen can be skipped.

== Trivia ==

* The music from the loading screen is called "[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8B1Xf58ws-4 Passing Through]", by Erick McNerney<ref name=":0">[https://erickmcnerney.bandcamp.com/ Erick McNerney's Bandcamp website] at ''erickmcnerney.bandcamp.com''; retrieved May 26, 2025</ref>.
** Erick McNerney has several official remixes of Passing Through on [https://www.youtube.com/@ErickMcNerney/videos his YouTube channel].
* The "Classic Warp Tunnel" was originally used until September 4, 2018, before being replaced by the Default modern loading screen.
** This particular loading screen is re-created in the [https://vrchat.com/home/world/wrld_bfb3e4ad-0952-48f6-82c8-23b66c340f4a/ VRChat Home - 10 Years] world.
** Partially Offline can also be heard in the [[VRChat Home]] music player.
* It might be speculated that the loading screen is a world called [https://vrchat.com/home/world/inbetween/info The In-Between].

